Master Xiangyan said: It is like a person up in a tree, with his mouth啣 biting a branch, his hands not grasping the branch,

his feet not stepping on the tree. Someone below the tree asks about the meaning of the coming from the West. If he does not answer, he goes against what is asked;

if he answers, he loses body and life. At just such a time, how should one answer?

Wumen said: In general, in investigating Chan and studying the Way, one must strictly avoid following sound and chasing form. Even

if you hear sound and awaken to the Way, or see form and illuminate the mind, this is ordinary. One does not know:

the Chan monk’s family rides sound and covers form; in every head it is bright, in every step it is wondrous. Yet

even so, tell me: does sound come to the ear, or does the ear go to sound? Even if resonant

and silent are both forgotten, how at this point do you speak understanding? If you listen with the ear it will be hard to understand;

hearing sound at the place of the eye is only then intimate.
